  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are actively buying the dip as SPX broke below the 6570 gamma wall, with spot currently sitting between the flip level (6550) and the massive 6565 wall - this PIN regime setup is providing strong stabilizing flows that should cap further downside. The thick gamma wall cluster between 6560-6580 (76M+ combined GEX) is acting like a magnet pulling price back toward fair value, with dealers systematically buying into this -13.4% move over the past minute. Watch 6550 as the critical level - a break below flips dealers to short gamma where they'd amplify moves lower, but as long as we hold above, expect mean reversion back toward the 6580 max gamma level where dealers will resume selling.",
